OFBiz Data Warehousing
This component is intended to facilitate the Business Intelligence regarding your OFBiz implementation

A set entities for business intelligence analysis in a separate (OLAP, or DW) database, accessible, in the same way as the main OFBiz Transaction Database, via the delegator.

The new OLAP database, will contain all the entities necessary to do DataWarehouse analysis: dimensions, facts and star schemas (that are view-entities). The dimensions, facts and star schemas are defined according to best practices for datawarehouses and best practices for OFBiz: they are defined as standard entities using the xml entity defs; clear and consistent naming conventions are used and they are documented by meta data descriptions (in the entity def). The best practices for datawarehouses are mainly taken from the book "The Data Warehouse Toolkit - Second Edition" by Ralph Kimball. The data for dimensions and facts are maintained and kept up to date using standard OFBiz services and ECA rules.


Current Status

The main low level services to post data to the datawarehouse, to map the operational keys with the datawarehouse ones, and to manage history of data changes are already implemented; they will be improved as the datawarehouse will grow (e.g. performance enhancements). The following dimensions (and associateddata services) are currently defined:


Asset DimensionCountry DimensionCurrency Dimension
Customer DimensionDate DimensionOrganisation Dimension
Product DimensionStore DimensionSupplier Dimension


The following fact tables (and associate ddata services) are currently defined:


Inventory Item FactSales Invoice Item FactSales Order Item Fact


The following Star Schemas are currently defined:

Inventory Item Star SchemaSales Invoice Star SchemaSales Order Item Star Schema


Initialisation

You can initialize the OFBiz Data WareHouse by clicking on the button below: the dimension and fact tables will be populated automatically.

Then you can run the analysis using the report builder menu. The report builder is a very simple tool that allows you to run the analysis on all the star schemas defined in the system. Just select the fields (colums) using the checkboxes you want to see in the report and a simple report will be shown. According to the columns selected data will be aggregated (drill up/down).
